cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multi-label image classification using deep convolutional neural networks.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a joint image-label embedding using recurrent neural networks and can be trained end-to-end from scratch.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the classification of images based on semantic label dependencies and image-label relevance.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with multi-label classification of images, which is a common task in multimedia analysis.
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the classification of images based on multiple labels, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks.
